tle":"Hadith on Siyam: Many virtues of fasting for Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 7, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAllah said, \u2018Every deed of the son of Adam is for him, except for fasting. It is for Me and I will reward it.\u2019 Fasting is a shield, so when one of you fasts, he may\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3756,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/23\/ramadan-do-not-precede-fast\/","url_meta":{"origin":15275,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Do not fast days before Ramadan, unless a routine","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 23, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cLet not one of you precede Ramadan with one or two days of fasting, unless it is part of a man's fasting routine, so let him fast that day.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1815. S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1082\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5250,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/17\/fasting-ramadan-six-shawwal\/","url_meta":{"origin":15275,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: Recommendation to fast six days of Shawwal","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 17, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Ayyub reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever fasts the month of Ramadan and then follows it with six days of fasting in the month of Shawwal, it will be as if he has fasted for the entire year.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1164\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3783,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/24\/invitation-meal-i-am-fasting\/","url_meta":{"origin":15275,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: Politely refuse an invitation to eat if fasting","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 24, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Zuhayr reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf one of you is invited to a meal while he is fasting, then let him\u00a0say: Indeed, I am fasting.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1150 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u0646 \u0632\u0647\u064a\u0631 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":18469,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/03\/09\/dawud-most-beloved-sawm-siyam\/","url_meta":{"origin":15275,"position":4